body.name: COSMO COS-DIS6502 24 in. Dishwasher in Fingerprint Resistant Stainless Steel with Stainless Steel Tub

climatePledgeFriendly.details: ENERGY STAR Most Efficient recognizes the best of ENERGY STAR certified products with highest efficiency and maximum carbon reductions.

features: QUIET OPERATION: Built-in dishwasher features ultra-quiet operation at only 51 dB with exterior sound insulating pads pre-installed.

LARGE CAPACITY: 24 in. tall tub dishwasher accommodates up to 12 place settings to wash multiple dishes at once; upper rack to accommodate large or irregular-sized dishes; large capacity lower rack easily accommodates plates, bowls, and cookware

FUNCTIONS: 4 Wash Cycles featuring 2 Options, including Heated Dry; Touch-enabled control panel at top of the door makes operation effortless, easy access and wipes clean; Multiple filter system saves water and energy by separating soiled and clean water
CERTIFICATIONS: UL Listed, NSF/ANSI 184, ENERGY STAR certified to help you conserve energy and pay less for utilities
1-YEAR LIMITED: Our customer support team is based proudly in the USA; Product Dimensions: 23.75" (W) x 22.25" (D) x 33.75" (H); Electrical Requirements: 120V / 60Hz, 3-Prong Plug (NOT INCLUDED)
body.description: Save time and free your hands from endless scrubbing with Cosmo's COS-DIS6502 24 inch Top Control Tall Tub Dishwasher. Built with high-grade stainless steel inside and out, our dishwasher's multiple wash cycle functions ensure your dishes are spotless. All controls are touch-enabled and hidden away when the door is closed for a clean aesthetic. Integrated Smart Wash System auto detects partial or full loads and picks the correct wash cycle. For irregular or large-sized dishes, the Upper Rack can be adjusted 2 inches. Designed for efficiency, a low 45dB noise rating, and includes Energy Star and UL Listed certifications. Make this top control dishwasher in the stainless steel part of your kitchen. Requires 3-Prong Plug (NOT INCLUDED). 3/8 Pipe Fitting necessary for installation sold separately.

productInformation.name: Special Feature
productInformation.value: Multiple wash cycle functions ranging from: Pots & Pans, Normal Wash, China Crystal, Quick Wash, Rinse Only, Air Exchange, Steam Wash, Vortex Wash, Heating Dry, Sanitize, and Hi Temp Wash. Smart Wash System. Low 51 dB noise rating. See more

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 30, 2022
reviews.reviewText: To be on the safe side, supplied water and power to this unit. Ran it empty a couple of times to check for leaks. None present then installed. It looks great, got familiar with the touch controls. A little bit of a learning curve but when I figured it all out it makes sense. Exterior and tub are all stainless steel and look great.Cleans well and is unnervingly quiet. It was a great purchase!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Broke after six months of daily use.
reviews.reviewText: This washer did its job great for the most part. It would clean our dishes so long as we pre-scrubbed them before loading. Before the washer broke we noticed it would beep intermittently for no apparent reason. After six months the control panel at the top stopped functioning so we can no longer use the washer. Save yourself a future headache and buy something else.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 13, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Washes okay, but still need to rinse dishes fairly well first.Bottom rack has a design defect, does not roll smoothly. Have to lift it to make it slide in properly.Wheels do not fit correctly on the rims.Buttons also difficult to use.But it is very quiet when running.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars quiet and efficient
reviews.reviewText: This dishwasher is very quiet and can handle large dirty loads. The fingerprint resistant stainless steel looks great and lives up to its claim. I appreciate that the inner tub is also made of steel. Overall I am very happy with this purchase after using it for 2 weeks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 12, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quiet High End Quality for an economy price.
reviews.reviewText: Appears to be well built and the same High End design as other models twice this price.Will know more about this after a few months of use.The CEVA 5 day shipping was also faster than stated.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Finally got to unpackaging it only to find out that it does not dry my dishes at all!!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this at the beginning of my renovation finally got the renovation done and the dishwasher professionally installed only to find out that it does not dry my dishes at all. They are cold and soaking wet at the end of the cycle. Other than that works great. Was told that I have to go through the warranty. Just about over Amazon, selling stuff that they no longer ensure works.

reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars We received a defected product that throws a E4 code.
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. We purchased the range/dishwasher and hood together. Our cabinets were grossly delayed, just receiving them 2/1. We hooked up the dishwasher on 2/4/22 and ran it for the first time 2/5/22, 2/6/22 it gave a code of E4… we got on here and found the return window closed 1/31/22. My wife was very hesitant on getting this brand but I fell for the brilliant range. So I went with the set. I had not read the reviews, I just wanted to give Cosmo a shot. We do live cooking shows, I can’t Imagine explaining to our 3 million viewers about the whole in our new cabinets.
